Service Intelligence Omni-Channel Dashboard

Quickly identify the routing efficiency and agent performance across Omni-Channel routing and queues. Check on work volumes, accepted or declined work, average handle times, average speed to answer, percentage of service levels met, and more.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions

In the Channel Performance tab, you can see high-level details by clicking Omni-Channel. Select from filters to refine your view, and review high-level statistics. Charts show work volume by object type, status, and queue. Drill into details for each case.

ROUTING KPI
Total work items: Total number of work items across all objects and channels.
Accepted work: Offered work items that an agent accepted.
Declined work: Percent of work assigned to agents but not accepted.
Avg speed to answer (Sec): Percent of inquiries answered within a specified timeframe.
Avg handle time (Min): Amount of time an agent spends on the work item until it's closed.
Service level: Percentage of inquiries answered within a specified timeframe.
Total cost: Total cost based on hourly rate and handle time.
Work volume by object type: Total volume of work objects sorted by type.
Work volume by status: Total volume of work objects sorted by status.
Work volume by queue: Total volume of work objects sorted by queues.
